docs.lead_paragraph: The Aldermen took up the REYNOLD's Offal Contract business last evening. The report of the Committee on Public Health of the Board of councilmen was taken up and discussed by Aldermen MOTT, HERRICK, LORD, HOARDMAN and President ELY. No Cerision was arrived at. The report (which has passed the other Board_ was referred.

headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times CONGRESSIONAL PROCEEDINGS. PASSAGE OF THE LAND GRADUATION BILL. Letter from Capt. Ingraham. TFE WEST POINT / CADEMY BILL. THIRTY-THIRD CONGRESS......First Session. HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES. NEW-YORK LEGISLATRUE. ASSEMBLY.

docs.lead_paragraph: The bill to reduce and graduate the price of the public lands was ordered to be engrossed for a third reading, by a vote of 72 to 68. Mr. Cox moved to lay the bill on the table. Negatived--69 against 80.
